How to set up:

1. create google cloud mysql instance. Follow the steps in 
https://cloud.google.com/sql/docs/mysql/connect-container-engine

2. create container cluster. Make sure it has access to mysql.
for the last commit container cluster contains one node-pool which
contains 3 micro node.

Before deployment:

replace <project_id>, <region_id>, <sql_instance>
 in workflow/yamlfile and workfile/dockerfile with your ids.

How to deploy:

1. go to workflow folder
2. run bash launcher/start.sh <version_number>
